'''法式離場（French leave）''' 意指未徵得同意甚或未知會在場其他人士即逕自退場。<ref>''Brewer's Dictionary of Phrase and Fable'' (Millennium Edition; London: Cassell, 1999)</ref>在宴會中悄無聲息地離去以避免主人留客即是一例。軍人擅離職守也算數。<ref>{{cite book | title=From Hue & Cry to Humble Pie | author=Parkinson, Judy | publisher=Michael O'Mara Books | year=2000 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=m896sTRsJa4C | page=80| isbn=9780760735817 }}</ref>

該詞彙首見於[[1771年|1771年]]英法文化交相影響之時。

在法國，同義詞為''英式離場(filer à l'anglaise)''<ref>Anu Garg's A.Word.A.Day, September 8, 2008. http://wordsmith.org/words/chinese_puzzle.html {{Wayback|url=http://wordsmith.org/words/chinese_puzzle.html |date=20210213214618 }}</ref>似乎首見於19至20世紀。<ref name="FP">{{cite web | url=http://www.francparler.com/syntagme.php?id=105 | title=Filer à l'anglaise | publisher=Francparler | accessdate=September 7, 2012 | archive-date=2020-12-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201208100238/http://www.francparler.com/syntagme.php?id=105 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

==一開始的用法==
[[牛津英文字典|牛津英文字典]]釋義：客人（18世紀見用於法國，英國稍後沿用）離開婚宴而未向男女主人告辭。打趣用法為不告而別或先斬後奏。<ref>"the custom (in the 18th century prevalent in France and sometimes imitated in England) of going away from a reception, etc. without taking leave of the host or hostess. Hence, jocularly, to take French leave is to go away, or do anything, without permission or notice."</ref>該字典稱首次見用為：1771 SMOLLETT Humph. Cl. (1895) 238 他偷偷拐跑了個愛爾蘭人的新娘，隨即不辭而別。<ref>"He stole away an Irishman's bride, and took a French leave of me and his master".</ref>

在美加，其用詞為''愛爾蘭式再見(Irish goodbye)''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://slate.com/human-interest/2013/07/ghosting-the-irish-goodbye-the-french-leave-stop-saying-goodbye-at-parties.html|title=Don't say goodbye|website=Slate.com|date=3 July 2013|author=Seth Stevenson|access-date=2020-09-26|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126001730/https://slate.com/human-interest/2013/07/ghosting-the-irish-goodbye-the-french-leave-stop-saying-goodbye-at-parties.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==軍事用語==
該詞亦有軍中混日子開小差之義<ref>For the usage, see for example The war memoirs of Commandant Ludwig Krause 1899-1900, Cape Town 1996, p. 65.</ref>，沿用自英法相爭時期。西班牙語中，此詞也以法國為對象(''despedida a la francesa'')，可能始自拿破崙於[[伊比利半島|伊比利半島]]從事[[半島戰爭|半島戰爭]]時，法軍當時與西葡聯軍為敵。

